Installation of Ansible:
1) Install python 3.7 and python 3 depending on the one you want.  https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52677089/how-to-install-pip-for-python3-7-only
https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-install-python-3-7-on-ubuntu-18-04/#:~:text=How%20to%20Install%20Python%203.7%20on%20Ubuntu%20Installing,ready%20to%20be%20used.%20You%20can...%20See%20More.
		curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py
		sudo apt update
		sudo apt install software-properties-common
		sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
		sudo apt install python3.7
		sudo apt install python3-pip
2) To check if Pip and Python have been installed we use:
		python3.7 -V && pip3 -V
and output expected is:
		Output:
		Python 3.7.3
		pip 19.1.1 from /usr/local/lib/python3.7/dist-packages/pip (python 3.7)
3) Install Ansible using: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/questions/ansible-problem-shared-connection-to-server-closed OR https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/ansible-introduction-and-installation-in-linux/
		sudo apt-add-repository -y ppa:ansible/ansible 
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install -y ansible

